'''Clas [[Myrddin]]''', or [[Merlin]]'s Enclosure, is an early name for [[Great Britain]] given in the Third Series of [[Welsh Triads]].<ref>Rhys: Hibbert Lectures, p. 168.</ref> It is implied that it is the oldest name, as opposed to "[[Albion]]", but the implication is not wholly credible.<ref>Stephen Thomas Knight, ''Merlin: Knowledge and Power Through the Ages'', p. 6</ref>

