[[File:Oceanias_Regions.png|right|thumb|upright=1.75|Oceania]] This article is a gallery of the flags of the principal subdivisions of the countries and territories of [[Oceania]]. For purposes of this article, Oceania is taken to comprise [[Australasia]], [[Melanesia]], [[Micronesia]] and [[Polynesia]].
The principal subdivisions are generally the ones that are identified as first-order subdivisions under the [[ISO 3166-2]] coding scheme. If a country has no such first-order subdivisions, but has second-order subdivisions that have their own official flags, then the flags of those second-order subdivisions are given here.
This gallery includes only current official flags. For historical or non-official flags of any particular country or territory (if any), see the main article for that country or territory.
Unless indicated otherwise, information on each country has been taken from the ''[[The World Factbook|World Factbook]]'', as updated through July 11, 2016 (for which see the External Links section, below).<ref>{{cite web|title=The World Factbook|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/resources/the-world-factbook/|website=cia.gov|publisher=Central Intelligence Agency|access-date=July 25, 2016}}</ref> {{TOC limit|3}}
==Australasia==
===Australia=== {{Main article|List of Australian flags#States and territories}} {{See also|States and territories of Australia}}
[[Australia]] comprises six states and two territories, as well as several dependant islands located in the Indian and Pacific oceans.
The official flag for each of the six states consists of the Australian national flag, but with the stars removed and replaced with the state's coat of arms.
Most of the dependent areas (sometimes called the "external territories") have no official flag of their own and instead use the Australian national flag. Three external territories do have their own official flags–[[Christmas Island]], [[Cocos (Keeling) Islands]], and [[Norfolk Island]].
====States==== {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of New South Wales.svg|[[Flag of New South Wales|New South Wales]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The New South Wales State Flag (1876) |url=https://www.anfa-national.org.au/australian-red-ensign/nsw/ |website=anfa-national.org.au |publisher=Australian National Flag Association |access-date=10 May 2018}}</ref> |File:Flag of Queensland.svg|[[Flag of Queensland|Queensland]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Queensland State Flag (1876) |url=https://www.anfa-national.org.au/australian-red-ensign/nsw/qld/ |website=anfa-national.org.au |publisher=Australian National Flag Association |access-date=10 May 2018}}</ref> |File:Flag of South Australia.svg|[[Flag of South Australia|South Australia]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The South Australian State Flag (1904) |url=https://www.anfa-national.org.au/australian-red-ensign/nsw/sa/ |website=anfa-national.org.au |publisher=Australian National Flag Association |access-date=10 May 2018}}</ref> |File:Flag of Tasmania.svg|[[Flag of Tasmania|Tasmania]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Tasmanian State Flag (1876) |url=https://www.anfa-national.org.au/australian-red-ensign/nsw/tas/ |website=anfa-national.org.au |publisher=Australian National Flag Association |access-date=10 May 2018}}</ref> |File:Flag of Victoria (Australia).svg|[[Flag of Victoria|Victoria]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Victorian State Flag (1877) |url=https://www.anfa-national.org.au/australian-red-ensign/nsw/vic/ |website=anfa-national.org.au |publisher=Australian National Flag Association |access-date=10 May 2018}}</ref> |File:Flag of Western Australia.svg|[[Flag of Western Australia|Western Australia]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Western Australian State Flag (1870) |url=https://www.anfa-national.org.au/australian-red-ensign/nsw/wa/ |website=anfa-national.org.au |publisher=Australian National Flag Association |access-date=10 May 2018}}</ref> }}
====Territories==== {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of the Australian Capital Territory.svg|[[Flag of the Australian Capital Territory|Australian Capital Territory]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Australian Capital Territory Flag (1993) |url=https://www.anfa-national.org.au/australian-red-ensign/nsw/act/ |website=anfa-national.org.au |publisher=Australian National Flag Association |access-date=10 May 2018}}</ref> |File:Flag of the Northern Territory.svg|[[Flag of the Northern Territory|Northern Territory]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Northern Territory Flag (1978) |url=https://www.anfa-national.org.au/australian-red-ensign/nsw/nt/ |website=anfa-national.org.au |publisher=Australian National Flag Association |access-date=10 May 2018}}</ref> }}
====Dependent areas==== {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of Christmas Island.svg|[[Flag of Christmas Island|Christmas Island]]<ref>{{cite web |title=The Flag of the Territory of Christmas Island |website=shire.gov.cx |publisher=[[Shire of Christmas Island]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150302155734/http://www.shire.gov.cx/ciflag.html |url=http://www.shire.gov.cx/ciflag.html |archive-date=2 March 2015 }}</ref> |File:Flag of Cocos (Keeling) Islands.svg|[[Flag of Cocos (Keeling) Islands|Cocos (Keeling) Islands]] |File:Flag of Norfolk Island.svg|[[Flag of Norfolk Island|Norfolk Island]]<ref>{{cite web| title=Norfolk Island Flag and Public Seal Act 1979 |url=https://www.legislation.gov.au/Details/C2015Q00187 |work=Federal Register of Legislation |publisher=Office of Parliamentary Counsel (Australia) |access-date=10 May 2018}}</ref> }}
===New Zealand=== {{main article|List of New Zealand flags}} {{See also|Regions of New Zealand}} {{See also|Realm of New Zealand}} [[New Zealand]] has sixteen first-level administrative subdivisions. Eleven of them are governed by regional authorities; the other five are governed by unitary authorities (which combine the roles of regional and territorial governance). The [[Chatham Islands]] lie outside any of the sixteen regions, but collectively possess some of the governing authority of a region. Most of these seventeen authorities have not adopted official flags.
The Realm of New Zealand includes two non-self-governing territories, one of which ([[Tokelau]]) has its own official flag. The other, the [[Ross Dependency]], does not. It also includes the two island nations that are in [[associated state#States in a formal association|free association]] with New Zealand–the [[Cook Islands]] and [[Niue]]. Their official flags are shown here.
====Regions==== {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Nelson flag.svg|[[Flag of the City of Nelson|City of Nelson]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Purchase a Civic Flag |website=nelson.govt.nz |url=http://nelson.govt.nz/council/council-structure/council-organisations-2/city-of-nelson-civic-trust/purchase-a-civic-flag/ |publisher=[[Nelson City Council]] |access-date=11 May 2018}}</ref> |File:Flag of Otago.svg|[[Flag of Otago|Otago]] }}
