==Melanesia==
===Fiji=== {{See also|Local government of Fiji}} [[Fiji]] is subdivided into fourteen provinces, which are loosely aggregated into four "divisions". There is also a self-governing dependency, [[Rotuma]]. None of these administrative units has adopted an official flag.
===French collectivities in Melanesia=== {{main article|Flags of the regions of France}} {{see also|Overseas departments and territories of France}} One of France's overseas regions is located in Melanesia. This region is [[New Caledonia]], which is a special-status [[collectivity]] of France. It has a flag that shares its official status with that of the French [[French flag|tricolor]]. {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Pro-Independence Flag of New Caledonia.svg|[[Flag of New Caledonia|New Caledonia]] }}
===Indonesia=== {{see also|Provinces of Indonesia}} The administration of [[Indonesia]] is divided amongst 34 provinces, four of which are located in Melanesia (the others are located in [[Southeast Asia]]). The four Melanesian provinces are [[Maluku (province)|Maluku]], [[North Maluku]], [[Papua (province)|Papua]] and [[West Papua (province)|West Papua]]. It is unclear whether any of these provinces has adopted an official flag.
===New Caledonia=== {{Main article|Flag of New Caledonia#Provincial flags}} [[New Caledonia]] is a special-status [[collectivity]] of France, divided administratively into three provinces. Each has its own official flag. {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Bandera Province Sud.svg |South Province |File:Drapeau Province Nord Nouvelle Calédonie.svg|North Province |File:Bandera Loyauté.png|Loyalty Islands }}
===Papua New Guinea=== {{See also|Provinces of Papua New Guinea}} [[Papua New Guinea]] is divided into twenty provinces plus a national capital district (i.e., [[Port Moresby]]) and [[Autonomous Region of Bougainville|Bougainville]], an autonomous region. Each has its own official flag.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vexilla-mundi.com/papua_new_guinea_divisions.html|title=Papua New Guinea–22 Provinces|website=vexilla-mundi.com|accessdate=August 29, 2016}}</ref>
====Provinces==== {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of Central Province PNG.svg|Central Province |File:Flag of East New Britain.svg|East New Britain |File:Flag of East Sepik.png|East Sepik |File:Flag of Eastern Highlands.svg|Eastern Highlands |File:Flag of Enga.png|Enga |File:Flag of Gulf Province.png|Gulf |File:Flag of Hela.svg|Hela |File:Flag of Jiwaka.svg|Jiwaka |File:Flag of Madang.svg|Madang |File:Flag of Manus.svg|Manus |File:Flag of Milne Bay.svg|Milne Bay |File:Flag of Morobe.png|Morobe |File:Flag of New Ireland.svg|New Ireland |File:Flag of Flag Oro new.png|Oro |File:Flag of Sandaun.svg|Sandaun |File:Flag of Chimbu.svg|Simbu |File:Flag of Southern Highlands Province (Papua New Guinea).svg|Southern Highlands |File:Flag of West New Britain.svg|West New Britain |File:Flag of Western Highlands.svg|Western Highlands |File:Flag of Western Province PNG.svg|Western Province }}
====Districts and autonomous regions==== {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of NCD.svg |National Capital District |File:Flag of Bougainville.svg |Autonomous Region of Bougainville }}
===Vanuatu=== {{See also|Provinces of Vanuatu}} [[Vanuatu]] is divided administratively into six provinces. Each province has its own official flag.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vexilla-mundi.com/vanuatu_divisions.html|title=Vanuatu - 6 Provinces|website=vexilla-mundi.com|accessdate=September 1, 2016}}</ref>
==Micronesia==
===Federated States of Micronesia=== {{see also|Administrative divisions of the Federated States of Micronesia}} The [[Federated States of Micronesia]] is a federal republic that has entered into a [[compact of free association]] with the United States. It has four states, each of which has its own official flag.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vexilla-mundi.com/micronesia_divisions.html|title=Micronesia–4 States|website=vexilla-mundi.com|accessdate=August 29, 2016}}</ref> {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of Chuuk.svg|Chuuk |File:Flag of Kosrae.svg|Kosrae |File:Flag of Pohnpei.svg|Pohnpei |File:Flag of Yap.svg|Yap }}
===Guam=== [[Guam]] is a self-governing territory of the United States. It has no first-order administrative divisions.
===Kiribati=== {{see also|Kiribati#Administrative divisions}}
Although [[Kiribati]] is split geographically into three areas (the [[Gilbert Islands]], the [[Line Islands]] and the [[Phoenix Islands]]), these geographic divisions are not used for administration. Administrative units exist at the district and island levels, but none are first-order administrative subdivisions.
===Marshall Islands=== The [[Marshall Islands]] is a federal republic that has entered into a [[compact of free association]] with the United States. There are no first-order administrative subdivisions.
===Nauru=== {{See also|Nauru#Administrative divisions}} [[Nauru]] is divided into fourteen administrative districts, none of which has an official flag.
===Northern Mariana Islands=== The [[Northern Mariana Islands]] are a self-governing territory of the United States. There are no first-order administrative subdivisions.
===Palau=== {{See also|States of Palau}} [[Palau]] is a republic that has entered into a [[compact of free association]] with the United States. It is composed of sixteen states, each of which has its own official flag.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vexilla-mundi.com/palau_divisions.html|title=Palau–16 States|website=vexilla-mundi.com|accessdate=August 29, 2016}}</ref> {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of Aimeliik.svg |Aimeliik |File:Flag of Airai State.png |Airai |File:Flag of Angaur State.png |Angaur |File:Flag of Hatohobei.svg |Hatohobei |File:Flag of Kayangel State.png |Kayangel |File:Flag of Koror State.png |Koror |File:Flag of Melekeok.png |Melekeok |File:Flag of Ngaraard State.png |Ngaraard |File:Flag of Ngarchelong.svg |Ngarchelong |File:Flag of Ngardmau State.png |Ngardmau |File:Flag of Ngatpang State.png |Ngatpang |File:Flag of Ngchesar State.png |Ngchesar |File:Flag of Ngeremlengui State.png |Ngeremlengui |File:Flag of Ngiwal State.png |Ngiwal |File:Flag of Peleliu State.png |Peleliu |File:Flag of Sonsorol.svg |Sonsorol }}
===United States in Micronesia=== {{Main article|History of the flags of the United States#Territorial and commonwealth flags}} {{Main article|History of the flags of the United States#Associated state flags}} {{See also|Territories of the United States}} The [[United States]] has three territories in Micronesia. Two of them (Guam and the Northern Mariana Islands) are self-governing and have their own official flags. The third (Wake Island) is not self-governing and uses the [[flag of the United States]] as its official flag.
Three Micronesian nations have entered into a [[compact of free association]] with the United States. These are the Federated States of Micronesia, the Marshall Islands and Palau.
====Territories==== {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of Guam.svg |[[Flag of Guam|Guam]] |File:Flag of the Northern Mariana Islands.svg |[[Flag of the Northern Mariana Islands|Northern Mariana Islands]] |File:Flag of the United States.svg |Wake Island }}
====Micronesian nations in free association with the United States==== {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of the Federated States of Micronesia.svg |[[Flag of the Federated States of Micronesia|Federated States of Micronesia]] |File:Flag of the Marshall Islands.svg |[[Flag of the Marshall Islands|Marshall Islands]] |File:Flag of Palau.svg |[[Flag of Palau|Palau]] }}
===Wake Island=== [[Wake Island]] is a territory of the United States. It has no first-order administrative subdivisions.
==Polynesia==
===American Samoa=== [[American Samoa]] is a territory of the United States. It has no first-order administrative subdivisions.
===Chilean territory in Polynesia=== [[Chile]] has one territory in Polynesia, [[Isla de Pascua]] (also known as Easter Island). However, it is administered as a province in the country's [[Valparaiso region]], and not as a first-order subdivision of Chile.
===Cook Islands=== The [[Cook Islands]] are a nation that is in free association with New Zealand. It has no first-order administrative subdivisions.
===French collectivities in Polynesia=== {{main article|Flags of the regions of France}} {{see also|Overseas departments and territories of France}}
There are two French [[collectivity|collectivities]] in Polynesia—[[French Polynesia]] and [[Wallis and Futuna]]. French Polynesia has a flag that shares its official status with that of the French [[Flag of France|tricolor]]; Wallis and Futuna does not. Also, [[Clipperton Island]] is a French territory in Polynesia, but not a collectivity. It is uninhabited and does not have its own official flag. {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of French Polynesia.svg |[[Flag of French Polynesia|French Polynesia]] }} ===French Polynesia=== {{see also|Administrative divisions of French Polynesia}} [[French Polynesia]] is an overseas [[collectivity]] of France. It consists of six archipelagos: the [[Austral Islands]], the [[Gambier Islands]], the [[Marquesas Islands]], the [[Tuamotus|Tuāmotu Islands]], plus the [[Leeward Islands]] and the [[Windward Islands]] (the last two collectively formerly known as the [[Society Islands]]). Although French Polynesia has no first-order administrative subdivisions within the meaning of the [[ISO 3166-2]] coding scheme, there are five second-order subdivisions that correspond to each of the archipelagos, except that the Gambier and Tuāmotu Islands are combined into a single administrative division. None of these divisions has adopted an official flag. However, a 1985 territorial decree permits the official use, alongside the French [[Flag of France|tricolour]] and the French Polynesian flag, of the official flag of the archipelago on which the flags are displayed.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Territorial Flag|website=presidence.pf|url=http://www.presidence.pf/index.php?88|archive-date=February 17, 2003|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20030217024916/http://www.presidence.pf/index.php?88}}</ref> Four of the archipelagos have adopted such official flags.<ref>{{cite web|title=La Polynesie Francaise - Histoire et Culture|publisher=Embassy of French Polynesia in China|archive-date=April 6, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090406011131/http://www.tahitinui.cn/fr/1_2_3.htm|website=tahitinui.cn|url=http://www.tahitinui.cn/fr/1_2_3.htm}}</ref> The two that have not are the Leeward Islands and the Windward Islands. {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of the Austral Islands.svg |[[Flag of the Austral Islands|Austral Islands]] |File:Flag of the Gambier Islands.svg |[[Flag of the Gambier Islands|Gambier Islands]] |File:Flag of Marquesas Islands.svg |[[Flag of the Marquesas Islands|Marquesas Islands]] |File:Flag of the Tuamotu Islands.svg |Tuāmotu Islands<ref>{{cite web|url=https://flagspot.net/flags/pf-tg-tm.html|title=Tuamotu Islands (Tuamotu and Gambier Islands, French Polynesia)|website=flagspot.net|publisher=Flags of the World|accessdate=August 29, 2016}}</ref> }}
===Niue=== [[Niue]] is a nation that is in free association with New Zealand. It has no first-order administrative subdivisions.
===Pitcairn Islands=== The [[Pitcairn Islands]] are a territory of the United Kingdom. There are no administrative subdivisions.
===Samoa=== {{See also|Districts of Samoa}} [[Samoa]] is divided administratively into eleven districts. None of them have adopted an official flag.
===Tokelau=== [[Tokelau]] is a self-administering territory of New Zealand. It has no administrative subdivisions.
===Tonga=== {{See also|Administrative divisions of Tonga}} [[Tonga]] is a constitutional monarchy composed of five administrative divisions. None of them have adopted official flags.
===Tuvalu=== {{See also|Administrative divisions of Tuvalu}} [[Tuvalu]] is a nation administered by seven island councils, plus one town council ([[Funafuti]]). None of these councils has adopted an official flag.
===United Kingdom in Polynesia=== The [[Pitcairn Islands]] are the only [[British Overseas Territories|British overseas territory]] in Oceania. It has an official flag. {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of the Pitcairn Islands.svg |[[Flag of the Pitcairn Islands|Pitcairn Islands]] }} ===United States in Polynesia=== {{Main article|History of the flags of the United States#Territorial and commonwealth flags}} {{See also|Territories of the United States}} [[Hawaii]], one of the fifty [[United States]], is located in Polynesia, as is one of the territories of the United States ([[American Samoa]]).
Seven of the nine islands in the [[United States Minor Outlying Islands]] group are located in Polynesia. These are [[Baker Island]], [[Howland Island]], [[Jarvis Island]], [[Johnston Atoll]], [[Kingman Reef]], [[Midway Atoll]] and [[Palmyra Atoll]]. None have a permanent population and all use the [[flag of the United States]] as their official flags.
====States and territories==== {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of Hawaii.svg |[[Flag of Hawaii|Hawaii]] |File:Flag of American Samoa.svg |[[Flag of American Samoa|American Samoa]] }} ===Wallis and Futuna=== {{Main article|Flag of Wallis and Futuna#Subdivision flags}} {{See also|Subdivisions of Wallis and Futuna}} [[Wallis and Futuna]] is a collectivity of France. It is composed of three precincts—[[Alo (Wallis and Futuna)|Alo]], [[Sigave]] and [[Uvea]]—each corresponding to a traditional kingdom. {{gallery |captionstyle=text-align:center |width=120|height=80 |File:Flag of Alo.svg |Alo |File:Flag of Sigave.svg |Sigave |File:Flag of Uvea.svg |Uvea }} ==See also== *[[Flags of Oceania]] (a gallery of national-level flags)
