This '''List of BBC Radio Sherlock Holmes dramatisations''' summarises the [[BBC Radio 4]] radio dramatisations of the complete [[Sherlock Holmes]] stories, with [[Bert Coules]] as head writer, and featuring [[Clive Merrison]] as Holmes and [[Michael Williams (actor)|Michael Williams]] as Watson. Together, the two actors completed radio adaptations of every story in the canon between 1989 and 1998. The complete canonical run is available on CD and audio cassette, as well as downloads.
==''A Study In Scarlet''== {{Main|A Study In Scarlet}} Two one-hour episodes recorded October 1989, at [[Maida Vale Studios|BBC studios, Maida Vale]], London and first broadcast on 5 and 12 November 1989.
