This is a list of [[People of United Kingdom|British]] [[supercentenarian]]s (people from the [[United Kingdom]] who have attained the age of at least 110 years). The [[Gerontology Research Group]] (GRG), an organization that tracks supercentenarians and validates their age claims, has asserted that there have been approximately 140 verified supercentenarians from the United Kingdom, the oldest of whom is [[Charlotte Hughes (supercentenarian)|Charlotte Hughes]] who died at the age of 115 years, 228 days. The oldest man ever from the United Kingdom is [[Henry Allingham]] who died at the age of 113 years, 42 days.<ref name="GRG">[http://www.grg.org/Adams/E.HTM GRG Validated Living Supercentenarians] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010224073235/http://www.grg.org/Adams/E.HTM |date=24 February 2001 }} The Gerontology Research Group (GRG) lists persons as living whose age has been validated and confirmed to be alive within the past year. Retrieved 9 January 2015.</ref><ref name="Supercentenarians who lived in the United Kingdom">[http://www.grg.org/Adams/L/UK.HTM GRG Verified Supercentenarian Cases - United Kingdom (As of 16 April 2007)] Retrieved 11 May 2011.</ref>
As of {{date}}, [[List of the oldest living people|the oldest living person in the United Kingdom]] is Grace Catherine Jones, born 16 September 1906, aged {{age in years and days|1906|9|16}}.<ref name="GRG WSRL">{{cite web |url= http://supercentenarian-research-foundation.org/TableE.aspx |title= Supercentenarian Data -- Table E |publisher= Gerontology Research Group |date= 22 July 2016 |accessdate= 22 July 2016}}</ref>{{failed verification|date=September 2018}}<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-45500594</ref>

